This paper is primarily focused on the computational aspects of isogenies, which are a useful tool in cryptography. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper involves algorithms and complexity analyses, which suggests that it could also fit into cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also involves algebraic proofs, which could place it in cs.DS (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.SD (Symbolic Computation and Algebraic Manipulation).
